      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Tord Romstad</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:160px;\"><a href=\"/File:TordTV.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/9/98/TordTV.jpg\" width=\"158\" height=\"228\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:TordTV.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Tord Romstad <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Tord Kallqvist Romstad</b>,<br />\na Norwegian algebraic geometer by education, and as chess and games programmer author of the <a href=\"/Category:Open_Source\" title=\"Category:Open Source\">open source chess programs</a> <a href=\"/Glaurung\" title=\"Glaurung\">Glaurung</a>, also available as <a href=\"/index.php?title=IPhone&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"IPhone (page does not exist)\">iPhone</a> chess program and since February 2014 as chess AI of <a href=\"/index.php?title=Play_Magnus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Play Magnus (page does not exist)\">Play Magnus</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, the didactic <a href=\"/Parallel_Search\" title=\"Parallel Search\">parallel search</a> engine <a href=\"/Viper\" title=\"Viper\">Viper</a>, the former <a href=\"/Gothmog\" title=\"Gothmog\">Gothmog</a>, and the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexagonal_chess\">hexagonal chess</a> program <i>Scatha</i>. Tord has also some interests in <a href=\"/Shogi\" title=\"Shogi\">Shogi</a> programming <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. In 2009 Tord joint forces with <a href=\"/Marco_Costalba\" title=\"Marco Costalba\">Marco Costalba</a> and <a href=\"/Joona_Kiiski\" title=\"Joona Kiiski\">Joona Kiiski</a> on Marco's initial branch of Glaurung's evolutionary tree called <a href=\"/Stockfish\" title=\"Stockfish\">Stockfish</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. Tord Romstad further developed various <a href=\"/Utilities\" title=\"Utilities\">chess programming libraries</a>, most recently the <a href=\"/index.php?title=Julia&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Julia (page does not exist)\">Julia</a> library <a href=\"/Chess.jl\" title=\"Chess.jl\">Chess.jl</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Photos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Photos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Photos\">Photos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Photos\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"https://de.chessbase.com/post/aronian-gewinnt-finet-che960-turnier\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Winners960WC2005.jpg\" src=\"/images/3/3d/Winners960WC2005.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div> \n<p>Winners <a href=\"/Chess960CWC_2005\" title=\"Chess960CWC 2005\">Chess960CWC 2005</a>: Tord Romstad, <a href=\"/Johannes_Zwanzger\" title=\"Johannes Zwanzger\">Johannes Zwanzger</a>, <a href=\"/Volker_B%C3%B6hm\" title=\"Volker Böhm\">Volker Böhm</a> and <a href=\"/Ralf_Sch%C3%A4fer\" title=\"Ralf Schäfer\">Ralf Schäfer</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=343084\">Mixing alpha-beta with PN search</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 18, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">Alpha-Beta</a>, <a href=\"/Proof-Number_Search\" title=\"Proof-Number Search\">Proof-Number Search</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=361766\">When to do a null move search - an experiment</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 26, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Null_Move_Pruning\" title=\"Null Move Pruning\">Null Move Pruning</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=516\">Two questions for bitboard experts</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, November 06, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">Bitboards</a>, <a href=\"/Square_Attacked_By#InBetween\" title=\"Square Attacked By\">In Between</a>, <a href=\"/Piece-Lists\" title=\"Piece-Lists\">Piece-Lists</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2005_...\">2005 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2005 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=2300&amp;p=10549\">Reductions and null move refutations</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, April 18, 2005&#160;» <a href=\"/Late_Move_Reductions\" title=\"Late Move Reductions\">Late Move Reductions</a>, <a href=\"/Null_Move_Pruning\" title=\"Null Move Pruning\">Null Move Pruning</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=485276\">A plea to all computer chess enthusiasts (absurdly long)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 08, 2006</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=4521\">Bitboard question</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, March 14, 2006&#160;» <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">Bitboards</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=13426\">Speedup with bitboards on 64-bit CPUs</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 27, 2007</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=135133&amp;t=15504\">The Art of Evaluation</a>  by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 2, 2007&#160;» <a href=\"/Evaluation_Philosophy\" title=\"Evaluation Philosophy\">Evaluation Philosophy</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=20646\">SEE problem</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 13, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Static_Exchange_Evaluation\" title=\"Static Exchange Evaluation\">Static Exchange Evaluation</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=21264\">Artificial stupidity - making a program play badly</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 20, 2008</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=35242\">Revolutionizing handheld chess: Glaurung 2 for the iPhone</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 02, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=51408&amp;start=5\">Re: Play Magnus: official App with Chess Engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 26, 2014&#160;» <a href=\"/index.php?title=Play_Magnus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Play Magnus (page does not exist)\">Play Magnus</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=65934\">Reactions about AlphaZero from top GMs...</a> by <a href=\"/Norman_Schmidt\" title=\"Norman Schmidt\">Norman Schmidt</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 08, 2017&#160;» <a href=\"/AlphaZero#Reactions\" title=\"AlphaZero\">Reactions From Top GMs, Stockfish Author</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=66630&amp;start=114\">Re: World Computer Chess Championship</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 28, 2018&#160;» <a href=\"/World_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"World Computer Chess Championship\">World Computer Chess Championship</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=75304&amp;start=5\">Re: Bit Board Orientation</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 06, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Square_Mapping_Considerations\" title=\"Square Mapping Considerations\">Square Mapping Considerations</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=75287&amp;start=48\">Re: Which of the many chess engines in this forum use b strategy&#160;?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 08, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Type_B_Strategy\" title=\"Type B Strategy\">Type B Strategy</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=77210\">Chess.jl – new version</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 30, 2021</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.stockfishchess.com/\">Stockfish Chess Engine Home</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/romstad/\">romstad (Tord Romstad) · GitHub</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://romstad.github.io/Chess.jl/dev/\">Home · Chess.jl</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.schach-welt.de/schach/computerschach/interviews/romstad-kiiski-costalba-eng\">Computerschach, Interview with Tord Romstad (Norway), Joona Kiiski (Finland) and Marco Costalba (Italy)</a> by <a href=\"/Frank_Quisinsky\" title=\"Frank Quisinsky\">Frank Quisinsky</a>, March 29, 2010</li>\n<li> <span id=\"Video\"></span><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tngtech.com/tng-ueber-uns/bigtechday/big-techday-8/abstracts.html#c12643\">Parallelism and Selectivity in Game Tree Search</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.tngtech.com/tng-ueber-uns/bigtechday/big-techday-8.html\">TNG | Big Techday 8</a>, June 12, 2015, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YouTube\">YouTube</a> Video <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <div class='embedvideo ev_inline ev_top autoResize' style=' width: 646px;'><div class='embedvideowrap' style='width: 640px;'><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/R0L3AuJUkk0?\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div></dd></dl>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://2017.flatmap.no/talks/romstad/\">flatMap(Oslo) - 2017 Tord Romstad - How Modern Chess Programs Work</a>, May 02, 2017</li></ul>\n<dl><dd> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://vimeo.com/216463393\">How Modern Chess Programs Work</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vimeo\">Vimeo</a> Video</dd></dl>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Tord_Romstad&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Tord Romstad during <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Chess_Championship_2014\">World Chess Championship 2014</a> in Norwegian TV, Capture from German <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/ZDF-Sportreportage\">ZDF Sportreportage</a>, November 23, 2014, with excerpts from the broadcast</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=51408&amp;start=5\">Re: Play Magnus: official App with Chess Engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 26, 2014</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.shogi.net/shogi-l/Archive/2007/Njan15-10.txt\">Some thoughts on computer Shogi</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, January 15, 2007</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.glaurungchess.com/shogi/usi.html\">The Universal Shogi Interface, draft 1 (2007-01-24)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://wbec-ridderkerk.forumotion.com/wbec-ridderkerk-news-info-f1/stockfish-glaurung-t402.htm\">Re: Stockfish - Glaurung</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Tord Romstad</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://wbec-ridderkerk.forumotion.com/forum.htm\">WBEC-Ridderkerk forum</a>, September 05, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://romstad.github.io/Chess.jl/dev/\">Home · Chess.jl</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.chessbase.com/post/aronian-gewinnt-finet-che960-turnier\">Aronian gewinnt FINet-Chess960-Turnier</a>, <a href=\"/ChessBase\" title=\"ChessBase\">ChessBase Nachrichten</a>, August 13, 2005 (German)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=59836&amp;start=3\">Re: Video&#160;: How do modern chess engines work&#160;?</a> by Hermann Krause, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 12, 2016</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><b><a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">Up one level</a></b>\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260301035614\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.023 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.025 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 153/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 344/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 26/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key oscar70_mw1-mw_:pcache:idhash:3600-0!canonical and timestamp 20260301035614 and revision id 25343\n -->\n"
